So i'll prob move the ticket (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/AUTO-532) to closed (or I can look into raising the clear error msg) and investigate slow loading to try and root cause and decide how quickly it should be fixed

And alrighty, I added the relevant bullets to our epic and marked the tickets that we want in by customer preview as `blocker`. I believe our goal is to get fixes in by end of this week for the weekend recert? Given there are a few blockers, is this possible? On BE side, I'm just looking into slow loading now, but I didn't make it as blocker (but can escalate if needed)

Thanks Pauline! Expectation we set with Sales/CEM was the pub preview changes would be stable and in sandbox by mon, prod the following monday. does that seem feasible?

cc: @Anil & @Serena for thoughts here as well.

I can probably do all the things that aren't the split classification extraction failure retry bug.

Everything else seems straightforward and I can get it in quickly

Retrying (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C0976HB6ZPT/p1756916879447719?thread_ts=1756913586.453429&cid=C0976HB6ZPT) didn't work after so many tries yesterday, but I just tried today (https://aihub-sandbox.internal.instabase.com/build/0198ec23-fd01-7c93-87ac-b6f65a07f4ca) and it's working :thinking_face: The recording also shows loading fields that are already extracted, and that's faster now too :0 with no changes.
